	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=6832&mid=110232468172349>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=6832&mid=110232468172349>RE: proc?</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=6832&mid=110232468172349#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Dec 6th 4:18 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=314508><span id=Scholar>clokverkorange, Eater of Souls</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>282 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.76]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You're right, but I think someone may get confused the way youre saying it.<br><br>&quot;Procs&quot; as you refer to them are actually effects. Effects usually have one of three triggers:<br><br>1. Triggered randomly during combat.<br>2. Trigged by right clicking the item.<br>3. Trigged upon equip, and stays until unequipped. <br><br>Additionally, right-clicking has two sub-categories:<br><br>2a. Can be clicked from a slot in inventory.<br>2b. Must be clicked while being worn. <br><br>Hope that helps someone.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>&lt;i&gt;Subtlety is the key to most battles.&lt;/i&gt;<br><br>\\--&lt;(&gt; o0o EVERQUEST o0o &lt;)&gt;--//<br>::Torvonnilus:: <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/profile.html?410935 target=akztarg>Lady Brenyaa Firestorm</a>(56/7 DEF Magician)<br>\\--&lt;(&gt; o0o EVERQUEST II o0o &lt;)&gt;--//<br>::Innothule:: <br><a href=HTTP://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=259793207 target=akztarg>Torden of Torvonnilus</a> 13 Human Crusader, Innothule &lt;Ogdru Jehad&gt;</td></tr>
